brewery.brewery_description: We are an independent artisan brewery based in the west of Ireland dedicated to the production of high quality, natural and full flavoured beers. All of our beers are craft brewed by combining the finest ingredients with traditional brewing techniques. The result is a beer that has received numerous awards, including being twice named as Ireland’s Best Beer.

beer.beer_description: Galway Girl is the title of the artwork created by Cathy Hughes, which we have decided to use as the name for our hazy IPA release. It's been brewed with Irish lager malt, and a generous helping of oats and wheat for a soft, fluffy base. The hops are the star of the show here though, with plenty of tropical, citrus, and pine notes coming from the Idaho 7 and Mosaic with a little bit of dank from the Strata. An intense and refreshing beer, enjoyable no matter how you're spending your time!

beer.beer_description: Galway Hooker was the first permanent pale ale to be produced in Ireland and is widely regarded as a leading light in the Irish craft beer sector. It has now firmly established itself as a favourite amongst beer enthusiasts.
Brewed in the traditional style of an India Pale Ale, this beer is packed full of citrus and tropical fruit flavours. Well suited to seafood, cured meats or dessert dishes
A malty Irish red ale on nitro. Exclusive to the King's Head, Galway, Ireland.
A silky smooth dark beer with roasted malt flavours and a rich coffee aroma. Ideally matched with hearty meat dishes and hard cheeses or as an after dinner drink.

Galway Girl is the title of the artwork created by Cathy Hughes, which we have decided to use as the name for our hazy IPA release. It's been brewed with Irish lager malt, and a generous helping of oats and wheat for a soft, fluffy base. The hops are the star of the show here though, with plenty of tropical, citrus, and pine notes coming from the Idaho 7 and Mosaic with a little bit of dank from the Strata. An intense and refreshing beer, enjoyable no matter how you're spending your time!

Amber in colour, this is an extremely well balanced and refreshing lager. An initial sweetness and nuttiness is followed by a clean and crisp finish. Recommended with spicy foods, chicken, pizza or simply on its own.

This unique beer is a collaboration between our brewery and locally based Leahy Beekeeping to bring you a special taste of the West of Ireland. It is a bronze coloured ale, providing earthy, woody and toffee flavours from the raw honey, complimented with grassy and floral notes from the hops.
Originally brewed in 2010. Revived in 2018, and again in 2022 as 'Organic Pilsner'. Occasionally rebadged as a house beer.

Released for the brewery's 10th and 15th anniversaries.

Brewed using seven varieties of hops, this pale coloured double IPA is brimming full of citrus and tropical flavours with a distinct floral aroma. Unfiltered and unpasteurised for a more robust and natural flavour.

Citrus is a West Coast IPA brewed using freshly squeezed lemon juice, lime juice and dried orange peels. Full of zesty citrus flavours, which are further enhanced with a generous addition of fruity hops. The beer is unfiltered and unpasteurised for a more robust and natural flavour.
A hazy IPA bursting with tropical fruit flavours and juicy hops, brewed using raw mango pulp.
House beer at Tig Chóilí, Galway.
Specially brewed to an ancient recipe for the Olde Castle Bar.

Not just a beer, but a journey in a can! Imagine cracking open this masterpiece and being greeted by a tantalizing aroma of tangerine, grapefruit, earthy pine, and ripe apricots. Each sip is a taste of paradise, with a harmonius blend of stone fruits, tropical delights, and just a hint of spice. But beware, the assertive bitterness will remind you that you're sipping on something truly heavenly. Get ready for an unforgettable experience with every sip of our double IPA!
A beautiful session IPA by the guys in Galway hooker brewery
A ruby black stout brewed using freshly pressed cherry juice and organic cocoa to produce a rich and complex flavour.

Our blackcurrant porter is made using Irish blackcurrants grown and harvested in Co. Wexford. It delivers a rich and unique taste with notes of vanilla paired with chocolate and a blackcurrant finish.
Brewed using locally foraged elderflower, this beer showcases earthy floral aromas with subtle pear and lychee flavours!
Brewed using raspberry and blueberry puree and a specially selected Belgian yeast, this lightly hopped ale showcases fruity, spicy and earthy flavours.
Limited edition. Launched February 2017.
